				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Best weapon money can buy?<a name="54533"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 30 04 8:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>With Bards potentially getting a large portion of their DPS from procs, I have to think that putting a nice proccing weapon in your main hand <i>may</i> beat the damage from a high ratio weapon like the VGLS.
<br />

<br />
What about a Dedgerex's Flintforged Cudgel?  Only 12/27, but a 622 pt proc.  At 305 Dex, that proc is worth ~21DPS.  With WA5, it's ~32DPS.  With SCF3, it's about ~35DPS.
<br />

<br />
It's kind of hard to estimating DPS considering all the Strength, Attack and AA bonuses, but I tend to parse about 25% higher than my estimates (based off the magic number) for my main hand, and 40% for my offhand.  This assumes 60% hit rate, 80% dual wield rate, 100% haste, 30% overhaste.
<br />

<br />
<u>Mainhand</u>
<br />
BDMG Estimate = 39 DPS
<br />
BDMG Actual ~ 42 DPS
<br />

<br />
<u>Offhand</u>
<br />
Epic Estimate = 26 DPS
<br />
Epic Actual ~ 23 DPS
<br />

<br />
<u>Mainhand</u>
<br />
VGLS Estimate = 44.3 DPS
<br />
Cudgel Estimate = 26.3 DPS + 21 DPS = 47.3 DPS
<br />
CHoS Estimate = 37.7 DPS + 6DPS = 43.7 DPS
<br />
Ethereal Destroyer Estimate = 40.3 DPS + 25 DPS = 65.3 DPS
<br />
DOoFM Estimate = 34 DPS + 10.6 DPS = 44.6 DPS
<br />
AHB Estimate = 44.3 DPS + 3.33 DPS = 47.6 DPS
<br />
LIB Estimate = 44-49 DPS + 5.33 DPS = 49.3-54.3 DPS
<br />
GBoS = 44.3 DPS + 6DPS = 50.3 DPS</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
