			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Best weapon money can buy?<a name="55358"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 6 04 12:20 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, mind, this is just my estimate formula.....
<br />

<br />
DAM = Weapon Damage
<br />
DLY = Weapon Delay
<br />
BON = Primary Hand Bonus
<br />
MAG = Magic Number = 2*DAM+BON
<br />
MIN = Minimum Hit = BON + 1
<br />
MAX = Max Hit = 6*DAM + BON -1
<br />
AVG = Average Hit
<br />
ACCY = Hit Accuracy (60%)
<br />
DW = Dual Wield % (1 for mainhand, 0.8 for offhand)
<br />
HASTE = Haste (no haste = 100%)
<br />
DA = Harmonious Attack (120% for HA5)
<br />

<br />
I have a set of constants K, which attempt to weight the number of hits at MIN, MAG, MAX and in between.
<br />

<br />
My 65 Hard LDON constants are:
<br />
K1 = 0.10
<br />
K2 = 0.00 (rarely hit for MIN)
<br />
K3 = 0.10
<br />
K4 = 0.54
<br />
K5 = 0.26
<br />

<br />
My VT constants are:
<br />
K1 = 0.07
<br />
K2 = 0.16 (hit for MIN alot)
<br />
K3 = 0.00 (rarely hit for MAX)
<br />
K4 = 0.38
<br />
K5 = 0.40
<br />

<br />
These constants change based on your ATK, and mob defense.  As your ATK increases, you will end up with a greater % of MAX hits and virtually no MIN hits.  As mob defense increases, you will end up a larger percentage of MIN hits and lesser MAX hits.
<br />

<br />
AVG = K1*MAG + K2*MIN + K3*MAX + K4*((MAG+MAX)/2) + K5*((MIN+MAG)/2)
<br />

<br />
DPS = 10*DA*HASTE*ACCY*DW*AVG/DLY</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Leamhanach
66-82 Half-Elf Bard</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
